title: Grateful Dead Live at Knickerbocker Arena on 1991-03-23
description: Jack Straw, Bertha, Walkin' Blues, Friend Of The Devil, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Loser, Cassidy, New Speedway Boogie Iko Iko, Saint Of Circumstance, Ship of Fools, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Jam-> All Along The Watchtower-> Morning Dew-> One More Saturday Night, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text:
Sbd? This is a great show, amazing Jack Straw, but this quality is horrible! Any sbd's available of this show, if so would love to see it up here. Thanks
4 stars for show
1 start for quality

Memories of Albany I had alot of hassles getting to this show but it was all worthwhile when they came out of space. Jerry shreds in Watchtower and then brings it down to get that right D note to start Morning Dew. What a DEW it was, best I've ever seen, the jam before the last verse is so hot you think they're not gonna sing the last verse and just end it, but no, they bring it right down to a whisper quiet jam with one solitary light from above bathing Jerry as he quietly weaves his way through the Dew and up and up and up 'till you think the song is gonna explode and BAM, right into Saturday Night. Yummy.
PS the sound IS bad, but the show is worth it.
Albany 1991 This was a good show!  The sound quality, or lack of quality, is terrible.  We need a SBD here, Please.  Not worth the time or money to download.

Front row and center, first show! This was my first show!  I was 16 and my ticket was front row and center!!!! Oh God!  I can't even describe the energy!  They were truely sound wizards and their boiling cauldrons were their amps!!!! Some of the notes Phil played during Space shoke my body, literally!  The whole experience was powerful!

Of course, my sister had tickets for the following night. She also sat in the same spot only her seats were  next to Rick Danko and Mountain Girl!!!! Lucky!

First show Hey stuffyhead, this was my first show too!  Funny...I was in the LAST row on the floor.  I remember thinking, why the hell do they have chairs here?  Who wants to sit?  The drums/space and Dew blew my mind and the rest was history.
Lucky spring... Got real lucky this spring and recieved mail order tickets for all shows. Musically Albany was not the best run. But had a blast all 3 nights. Check out Morning Dew here.
